definition: and/furthermore/also/together with/(not) at all/simultaneously/to combine/to join/to merge

sentences.english: Life won't always turn out the way you want.
sentences.chinese: 生活並不總會如你所願。

sentences.english: Newton's law is not applicable to any case.
sentences.chinese: 牛頓定律並不適合於任何情況。

sentences.english: The line was going out fast but steadily and the fish was not panicked.
sentences.chinese: 釣索朝水中溜得既快又穩，闡明這魚並不受驚。

sentences.english: According to Zhao, life in military campsites is not monotonous.
sentences.chinese: 趙峯表示，軍營生活並不單調。

sentences.english: Melbury did not seem to be particularly enlightened by this explanation.
sentences.chinese: 麥爾布禮看來對這個解釋並不很明白。

sentences.english: Tears don't mean you're losing, everybody's bruising.
sentences.chinese: 眼淚並不意味着你失去了，大家的青腫。

sentences.english: LJ says his parents aren’t home, but they will be soon.
sentences.chinese: LJ告訴他父母並不在家，但很快會回來的。

sentences.english: Of course, we don’t accept the unrealistic overstatement about reverse merger.
sentences.chinese: 當然我們並不認同那些片面誇大反向收購作用的作法。

sentences.english: Gray-matter maturity, however, does not signal the end of mental change.
sentences.chinese: 然而灰質的成熟並不標誌着智力變換的終結。

sentences.english: Light abolishes darkness merely by showing you it is not there.
sentences.chinese: 光明只要讓你看到黑暗並不存在。

sentences.english: Applying the market rule to electronic unfair competition disputes is not always easy.
sentences.chinese: 運用該市場規律來消除電子不正當競爭並不容易。

sentences.english: They don't really look like white elephants.
sentences.chinese: 看上去並不真象一羣白象。

sentences.english: Anderson has the attitude for comedy, but not the aptitude.
sentences.chinese: 導演有對於喜劇片的態度，但是也許並不正確。

sentences.english: But in a sentence, it may not always mean that.
sentences.chinese: 但是在句子中，並不永遠是這樣的情況。

sentences.english: The democracy of one dollar one vote is not attractive.
sentences.chinese: “一美元一票”的民主制並不具有吸引力。

definition: regarding/as far as sth is concerned/with regards to
after all/all in all/when all is said and done/in the final analysis
but/yet/however/while/to go back/to decline/to retreat/nevertheless/even though
only natural/as it should be/certainly/of course/without doubt
